> It's also not just the PHP parser, it's any file above 300 lines (or like, > 10kb).

@NikkieDev, please try to reproduce the issue; remember the file, the place and the action that breaks the parsing. Then, switch to a minimal config that just installs and starts a parser, and see if it breaks.

If the issue is with any file and any parser, I definitely can't reproduce (with the most minimal setup). But I also see that you store globals (`g:var`) in your sessions, which would break a lot of plugins I'm familiar with.
